  "text": "When reading a breast MRI, evaluation of the breast tissue, chest wall, skin, and axillary lymph nodes (LNs) should be performed primarily. However, all other anatomical structures in the field of view (FOV) such as the neck, lung, mediastinum, spine, rib, sternum, and upper abdomen should not be overlooked because these will be the potential site of metastasis. Dietzel et al. has shown sufficient diagnostic accuracy detecting distant metastasis by simply extending the FOV to the hyoid bone and upper pelvis with a coronal sequence T2 half-Fourier acquisition single-shot turbo spin-echo image [CITATION_1] .",
